# Create Full Function VPC
1. Create VPC, and Route 
2. Create Private and Public subnet
3. Create Private and Public Route
# Create 2  EC2 Instance
4.  Create Public And Private Instance Assign Custome Network VPC and subnet


VPC Create = ostad-vpc = 12.0.0.0/16
Internet Getway Create = Ostad-IGW => Action => Attach 

Create subnet 
=== 
1. select vpc 
2. Subnet name 
3. Availability Zone 
4. IPv4 subnet CIDR block => 12.0.1.0/24

5. Create Route 
	1. Public Route Table

  	 name: my-public-route-table
   	VPC : ostad-vpc

	2. Private Route table

  	  name: my-privatec-route-table
   	VPC : ostad-vpc


	3. To get internet Create Rule Public Route Table 
	 ## click my-public-route-table => Edit routes => Add route => Destination= 0.0.0.0/0 ,Target= Internet Getway ,ostad-igq = Save


6. Select Subnet To the Route Table 
	# on Route table => Subnet associations => Edit subnet associations => Select subnet => save

7. Create EC2 instance 
  # public Ec2 
  # private Ec2 
note: must use custome subnet and network vpc

8. Connect private Ec2 using public Ec2 
# naming .pem file copy desktop to public ec2 
# permission = > chmod 400 beston.pem 
# Connect private => ssh -i beston.pem ubuntu@12.0.2.167 / ssh -i beston.pem 12.0.2.167

8. Need internet access to update some package on private ec2 
# Create NAT gateways on VPC Option 
 1. Create NAT gateway
 2. Name => my-nat ,Subnet = public-subnet
 3. Elastic IP allocation ID = > Allocate Elastic IP
9. Private Route = >Edit routes => Add route => Destination = 0.0.0.0/0 , Target= NAT gateway , my-nat 
Note: Becarefull must add NAT gateway , my-nat not Internet gateway







